title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1989-12-30
description:
Set 1

Bertha >
Good Lovin' >
Sugaree *
Walkin' Blues *
Jack A Roe *
When I Paint My Masterpiece *
West L.A. Fadeaway *
The Music Never Stopped *

Set 2

Jack Straw
China Cat Sunflower > *
I Know You Rider > *
Estimated Prophet > *
Terrapin Station > *
Drums > *
Space >
I Will Take You Home >
The Other One > *
Standing On The Moon > *
One More Saturday Night *

Encore:
It's All Over Now Baby Blue

Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums
Airto Moreira - Percussion *

reviews.review_text:
Great Concert ! Hey GD fans, 

I gotta say this show surpasses the new year's eve show.  Sometimes,  I like to think the GD looked out for the working man,  yeah, the guy who couldn't get the NYE ticket.  It seems the GD come out to play hard ... set one and set two are SOLID performance.  Bertha > Good Lovin' is always a good sign post 70's ! A rocking' 1st set with no real psychedelic tune like birdsong, cassidy, or let it grow.  You can hear the GD pushing the PA to the limit with serious bass bombs and some very slight squelch's of feedback.  However, I must say the PA sound , ain't that bad for Oakland Coliseum.  I've heard some really bad stuff there... 

The second set is turned up a notch or two since the expectation was so high after a really hot 1st set.  A little bit of a blast from the past with a Jack Straw opener, a tune mostly played in the 1st set by this point in their career.  Then a standard second set type set list occurs C. Cat > Rider, Estimated > Terrapin but really well played as if the GD were trying to impress some VIP's or friends, or maybe it's being able to play a gig and sleep at home, a welcome feeling from being on the road for months at a time.  

This source to my ears is the best for me ... Mattes has a really good rig and it sounds that way; there's a few hand claps but mostly it's a really nice recording.  I just wish the FOB guys could get the mic's over the crowd like the older days ... but what ya going to do?  This show is worthy of a commercial release... I'd love to hear the soundboard in earnest.  A marvelous performance as they meant it ...
Best Aud source Great show.  Sounds real nice for the Coliseum.
